OL,3,CPolice officers who shot man dead in
OL,4,CCarlisle granted anonymity
OL,6,FAn investigation by the Independent
OL,7,FOffice for Police Conduct found that
OL,8,Fseven shots were fired by two officers
OL,9,Fand found that both officers 'acted in
OL,10,Faccordance with their training' as
OL,11,Fthey told investigators they were
OL,12,Facting under the belief there was an
OL,13,Fimminent threat to the child's life.
OL,15,FCoroner Kirsty Gomersal ruled on 6
OL,16,FJune 2025 that granting anonymity
OL,17,Fwould not be a wholescale incursion on
OL,18,Fthe principle of open justice.
