OL,3,CPolice officers who shot man dead in
OL,4,CCarlisle granted anonymity
OL,6,FShe said that given the geography of
OL,7,FCumbria and small community that the
OL,8,Fofficers live and work in, the
OL,9,Fapplication was justified to protect
OL,10,Fthe privacy of the officers and their
OL,11,Ffamilies.
OL,13,FMs Gomersal also ruled that
OL,14,Fidentifying the two officers would
OL,15,Fhave a significant impact on their
OL,16,Fprofessional roles and career
OL,17,Fambitions as fire arms officers and
OL,18,Fclose protection officers, since their
OL,19,Fnames and photos would most likely
OL,20,Fbecome publicly available online.
